					In July of 2011, I moved to Japan. In July of 2012, I discovered my passion for building things. Since then I've been teaching English during the day and writing code every night.
				</p>	
				<p>
					I started out on the typical LAMP stack and soon branched out to try new things. Javascript is quickly becoming my forte, and I've recently grown quite fond of Ruby. I think Git is magnificent and Sublime Text 2 is awesome. I tend to consume APIs like they are going out of style. My goal is to become a well rounded, full stack developer, and I'd like to think I'm well on my way. Venturing outside my comfort zone is where I learn the most, and I try to get out there as much as possible.
